# Example udev rule for Yahboom Robot Expansion Board V3.0 (CH340 USB-to-Serial bridge).
# 
# 🛠️ Verification commands:
# 1. Run `lsusb` to check the actual idVendor and idProduct of the CH340 chip.
# 2. Run `udevadm info -a -n /dev/ttyUSB0` to query all attributes of the serial device node.
#
# If your board uses a different USB-to-Serial bridge chip (e.g. CP2102, FTDI), 
# update the idVendor and idProduct values accordingly.

SUBSYSTEM=="tty", ATTRS{idVendor}=="1a86", ATTRS{idProduct}=="7523", SYMLINK+="ttyUSB_ROSBOARD", MODE="0666"
